Package org.web3d.x3d.jsail.fields

Class MFVec3dObject

java.lang.Object
org.web3d.x3d.jsail.fields.X3DConcreteField
org.web3d.x3d.jsail.fields.MFVec3dObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
MField, MFVec3d, X3DField
public class MFVec3dObject
extends X3DConcreteField
implements MFVec3d
This utility class provides a concrete implementation corresponding to MFVec3d X3D field type.


Package hint: This specification class is defined by the X3D Java Language Binding Specification for the Scene Authoring Interface (SAI). MFVec3d is an array of SFVec3d values. Individual singleton SFVec3d array values are optionally separated by commas. Original rationale for inclusion: GeoVRML 1.0 Recommended Practice, Section 2.3, Limitations of Single Precision. Hint: MFVec3d can be used to specify a list of georeferenced 3D coordinates.

Related field object: SFVec3dObject
See Also:
X3D Tooltips: type MFVec3d, SAI Java Specification: B.4.11 X3DFieldTypes, SAI Abstract Specification: 5.2.15 SAIFieldType, X3D Abstract Specification: SFVec3dAndMFVec3d, X3D Tooltips, X3D Tooltips: field, X3D Tooltips: fieldValue, X3D Scene Authoring Hints
